        "name": null,
        "patch_url": null
      },
      "body": "Actually, as compilers are free to unroll the loop `for (group = ECMULT_CONST_GROUPS - 1; group >= 0; --group)` and allocate local variables in different places for each iteration, it is a bit unsound to do `if (group == 0) { /* clear variables */ }`.\r\n\r\nIf calling clear functions several times is an issue, it will make more sense to move the relevant variables (`t`, `neg_y`...) outside of the loop and to clear them after the loop. I did not do this, as I wanted to keep the changes small.",
      "created_at": "2026-06-29T18:55:25Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-29T18:55:42Z",
